Euri 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , Briſtonia, Leporinos Horreſcens vortices (i. e.) That ſhallow water fordable but now, is now raiſed to ſuch an height, that Bristol is ſwallowed up by the proud ſwelling waters of Hare-ford. This interpretation is literall too, and Allegoricall; one word onely is out of place, and improper, for it fits not the Allegory, yet is it very emphaticall;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
Briſtonia, Bristoll groanes under cruell bondage; It does indeed, ſuch as Iſrael never felt under Pharaoh, and his Task-maſters; nor the Chriſtian under the Turke;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 Briſtonia, That Citie knowes the ſenſe of that word now.
